### Pi create / exit mechanics

- Create: call the `worktree_start` tool with a prompt or explicit branch name; the
  `@rezamonangg/pi-worktree` package creates the worktree and routes subsequent
  write/edit/bash calls into it via path rewriting.
- Worktree path: `.worktree/<branch>`, branch inferred from task type
  (feat/, fix/, docs/, refactor/, test/).
- The `worktree-guard.ts` extension blocks mutations until a matching successful
  `worktree_start` result is validated. Root permits only `worktree_start`,
  `worktree_status`, and `worktree_stop`; workers receive a topology-validated initial
  cwd and use direct Git there. That launch check is not path containment: workers must
  remain inside their assigned worktree. Other `worktree_*` tools and every lifecycle
  tool in a child are blocked.
- Complete: call `worktree_stop` (optionally `remove: true`) only after an approved merge;
  its approval remains active unless the matching external stop succeeds.
- There is no worktree-exemption sentinel or human bypass.
{{- end }}
